query:
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `ab_test_results` (
  `id` int NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `testId` int NOT NULL,
  `variantId` int NOT NULL,
  `metricName` varchar(50) NOT NULL,
  `controlValue` decimal(10,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `treatmentValue` decimal(10,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `absoluteDiff` decimal(10,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `relativeDiff` decimal(10,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `pValue` decimal(10,6) DEFAULT NULL,
  `confidenceInterval` varchar(100) DEFAULT NULL,
  `isSignificant` tinyint(1) DEFAULT 0,
  `calculatedAt` datetime NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `idx_ab_test_results_testId` (`testId`),
  KEY `idx_ab_test_results_variantId` (`variantId`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4;
